{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d142b603-2779-4f82-a3ab-8c13cf40363d","content":"In .NET 10 (targeting Android 15 / API 35), `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is **ignored** because Android enforces edge-to-edge rendering. The fix is to react to **keyboard window insets** instead.\n\n**In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:**\n\n```csharp\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\n[Activity(/* ... existing attributes ... */,\n          WindowSoftInputMode = SoftInput.AdjustResize)] // still needed as a hint\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity\n{\n    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n    {\n        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;\n        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());\n    }\n\n    class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n    {\n        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n        {\n            var ime = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n            var bars = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());\n\n            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset\n            v.SetPadding(v.PaddingLeft, v.PaddingTop, v.PaddingRight,\n                         Math.Max(ime.Bottom, bars.Bottom));\n\n            return insets;\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Why this works:** `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` reports the keyboard height in real time. When the keyboard opens, `ime.Bottom` grows and pushes your content (including the input bar) upward. When it closes, the system-bar inset takes over so the nav bar is still respected.\n\n**Layout tip:** make sure your XAML uses a `Grid` with the input bar in the last row — the padding applied above will shift the entire content area up:\n\n```xml\n<Grid RowDefinitions=\"*, Auto\">\n    <CollectionView Grid.Row=\"0\" ... />\n    <Entry Grid.Row=\"1\" Placeholder=\"Type a message...\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\nNo extra NuGet packages needed — `AndroidX.Core` is already a transitive dependency of MAUI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"acfcaa74-0189-47bd-b902-5a124c06981c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue where the keyboard covers the bottom text input on Android. They mention that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer works in .NET 10 (previously used in .NET 9).\n\nThis is a known change in .NET MAUI / Android. In Android 11+ (API 30+), `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` was deprecated, and .NET MAUI has been moving toward using `WindowInsets` / edge-to-edge APIs instead.\n\nIn .NET 10 (which targets Android 15 / API 35), edge-to-edge is enforced by default, and `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` no longer has any effect. \n\nThe solution involves handling `WindowInsets` properly since the old `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` approach is no longer viable. While `android:windowSoftInputMode=\"adjustResize\"` can still be set in the AndroidManifest, it's not sufficient on its own—the real fix requires working with the new insets system that Android 15 uses. The real solution in .NET MAUI .NET 10 is to leverage the framework's built-in insets handling rather than relying on deprecated Android APIs—I need to use the safe area and keyboard inset listeners that MAUI now provides natively, which automatically adjust layouts when the keyboard appears without needing manual `adjustResize` configuration. Setting up the window insets listener...\n\nActually, I'm reconsidering the approach here. The core issue is that the keyboard is obscuring the input field at the bottom, and for .NET MAUI on .NET 10, the most reliable solution involves configuring how the system handles the keyboard layout adjustment. Let me think through what actually works in practice without overcomplicating it. Setting up the window insets listener...","outputTokens":2213,"requestId":"E831:171772:26A48B4:2AD3328:69F9430F"},"id":"ebc09c37-58d1-452c-8dde-745bed53755d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:09:12.006Z","parentId":"3308be80-a9f6-463a-9b85-a6210fc8ec18"}
